content: Health care is a critically important issue and very complicated. There is room for debate on all sides. So, why not get all the information you can on the subject before pushing legislation to fix it. The current Republican plan is being put to a vote without the CBO score and without a public debate on the floor. It wouldn't hurt and would only give the public a better understanding of what is being promoted. I think this should be the rule, regardless, of what party is running the government.
name: David Novarro

content: So, I have this evergreen tree outside my house and it took a beating after a recent storm. The poor thing is bent out out shape, but seems to still be healthy. However, I think it is getting worse because it looks like it seeking the sun through all the tree branches on the street. I feel like there is some  sort of analogy to life here
